[...]

I don't understand the fix.  When you disconnect the choke, the
engine starts.  But the position of the choke doesn't change because
all you've done is disconnect the heating element.

I sounds to me like the choke heating element is grounding the coil
when the element is cold.  After you disconnect the choke, no more
ground.  Once the engine and carb warm up, the bi-metallic strip
moves slightly and the short no longer occurs.

